09/11/2003
NEUSS, Germany -- Croatian President Stipe Mesic received a UNESCO Children's Pyramids Award at a ceremony in Neuss, Germany on Saturday (8 November). The UNESCO benefit gala celebrated the world's contribution to policies in support of children. The other awards went to former Polish President Lech Walesa, former Indonesian President Jusuf Habibie, model Waris Dirie, and Flavio Briatore, head of the Benetton-Renault Formula One racing team. (HINA, HRT - 08/11/03)
